03:21.066 --> 03:23.633
[cellphone vibrates]

03:23.633 --> 03:25.767
[beep]
-Jesus, Wags.

03:25.767 --> 03:27.500
When a guy says
sell everything,

03:27.500 --> 03:29.333
he gets a chance
to take it back.

03:29.333 --> 03:31.533
Fair enough. Not gonna.

03:31.533 --> 03:33.667
You gotta say it.

03:33.667 --> 03:35.000
I already said it.

03:35.000 --> 03:37.533
Do it smart, do it so we
don't get hurt, but do it.

03:37.533 --> 03:40.133
Once we're out of telecom,
we get out of tech.

03:40.133 --> 03:42.400
Look, if the investors
hear about this,

03:42.400 --> 03:45.333
they are gonna wonder
what the fuck is going on.

03:45.333 --> 03:48.000
No, they're not, 'cause you're
gonna call 'em and tell 'em.

03:48.000 --> 03:49.600
Tell 'em what?

03:49.600 --> 03:51.467
Tell 'em that
we're shutting down.

03:51.467 --> 03:54.433
Give them the heads up. They
can start looking elsewhere.

03:54.433 --> 03:56.467
And next week?
If you change your mind?

03:56.467 --> 04:00.000
Well, let's just
get through today. Bye.

04:00.000 --> 04:01.567
Please tell me that
this fine specimen

04:01.567 --> 04:03.533
is our line to Bobby Axelrod.

04:03.533 --> 04:06.166
He is. We just need to
link him to Pepsum.

04:06.166 --> 04:07.600
Then we'll flip him
against Axelrod.

04:07.600 --> 04:11.600
Mm. How is his, uh,
personal life?

04:11.600 --> 04:13.567
Dude, it's too perfect.

04:13.567 --> 04:16.033
"Dollar" Bill Stearn --
devoted family man.

04:16.033 --> 04:18.367
-Sunday school teacher.
-Volunteer fireman.

04:18.367 --> 04:21.300
Wow, I'm gettin'
all weepy-eyed.

04:21.300 --> 04:22.667
-Guess we gotta let him go.
[file thuds]

04:22.667 --> 04:25.266
-It hasn't even been a week.
-A week we got nothing.

04:25.266 --> 04:27.567
-We do have a theory.
-Finally! Thank you.

04:27.567 --> 04:30.767
-It's not fully worked out yet.
-But what Dale is referring to

04:30.767 --> 04:33.266
is, uh, Bill Stearn bribed

04:33.266 --> 04:35.700
the Pepsum researcher
for proprietary information

04:35.700 --> 04:37.567
on a drug called
Vaccarizine.

04:37.567 --> 04:39.600
It's an enzyme they've been
testing out in Iowa.

04:39.600 --> 04:42.233
Genetically modifies corn
so that cows can actually digest

04:42.233 --> 04:44.400
-without antibiotics and --
-It makes them shit better.

04:44.400 --> 04:46.233
I'm sorry, but does
this, uh, farm report

04:46.233 --> 04:48.266
wind up anywhere near
an arrest warrant?

04:48.266 --> 04:50.166
Well, we think that
there is a nexus

04:50.166 --> 04:52.200
between Stearn and the guys
who ran the test.

04:52.200 --> 04:54.166
We have to just
place Stearn in Iowa

04:54.166 --> 04:56.367
-at the right time --
-So no.

05:04.333 --> 05:05.467
[sighs]

05:05.467 --> 05:08.400
Don't tell him
part of the story

05:08.400 --> 05:10.467
until you know
the whole story.

05:10.467 --> 05:14.033
-Got it.
-[sighs deeply] All right.

05:14.033 --> 05:16.166
Let's go through
these bank records.

05:16.166 --> 05:17.233
[grunts]

05:17.233 --> 05:21.033
-Mm. Um...
-Yeah, what's up?

05:21.033 --> 05:22.400
[lowered voice] You still
keep emergency deodorant

05:22.400 --> 05:24.467
-in your office?
-Yeah, you need some?

05:24.467 --> 05:26.200
No.

05:31.333 --> 05:33.333
[clears throat]

05:34.500 --> 05:35.767
Grandma's recipe.

05:35.767 --> 05:38.500
Signature dish
at the Empire Diner.

05:38.500 --> 05:40.533
I thought Grandma
was a waitress.

05:40.533 --> 05:43.100
She knew her way around
a griddle, too.

05:43.100 --> 05:46.033
[Bobby] Gotta use
enough cinnamon.

05:46.033 --> 05:48.500
[utensils clinking]

05:50.633 --> 05:52.667
-Am I out of a job?
-Don't worry, Ryan.

05:52.667 --> 05:54.567
Breakfast is about
all I can handle.

05:54.567 --> 05:56.333
Yeah, trust me.
We need you back.

05:56.333 --> 05:58.467
Wow! [chuckles]
Ryan, take the morning off.

05:58.467 --> 06:00.333
-Be back for lunch?
-You got it.

06:00.333 --> 06:02.100
-Thanks.
[utensil clinks]

06:03.500 --> 06:05.734
[lips smack]
Family announcement.

06:05.734 --> 06:06.767
New boat's coming early.

06:06.767 --> 06:09.633
-The big one?
-Wow.

06:09.633 --> 06:11.200
[Bobby] Delivery
on Friday afternoon.

06:11.200 --> 06:14.500
Great. Thinking Europe,
end of summer?

06:14.500 --> 06:17.233
Mediterranean Milk Run? Nah.

06:17.233 --> 06:20.033
Can we go to the GalÃ¡pagos
to meet Lonesome George?

06:20.033 --> 06:22.000
Lonesome George is dead.

06:22.000 --> 06:24.667
Really? Oh, shit.

06:24.667 --> 06:26.200
Hey. Language.

06:26.200 --> 06:28.000
GalÃ¡pagos?

06:28.000 --> 06:30.200
GalÃ¡pagos. Nice.

06:30.200 --> 06:31.400
-How much sooner?
[mug clatters]

06:31.400 --> 06:33.667
-How 'bout next week?
[utensil clinks]

06:34.667 --> 06:36.166
Yeah, we can.

06:36.166 --> 06:38.000
[dishware clinking]

06:38.000 --> 06:39.567
If that's the thing
to do right now.

06:39.567 --> 06:41.567
Well, you know,
I was just thinking,

06:41.567 --> 06:44.567
boys will be out of school.
Perfect time in their lives.

06:44.567 --> 06:47.700
Well, maybe it's not
the perfect time in my life.

06:47.700 --> 06:50.033
Summer at the restaurant,
it's gonna be insane.

06:50.033 --> 06:51.166
All right, I get that.

06:51.166 --> 06:53.166
So we'll set something up
so you can stay in touch.

06:53.166 --> 06:55.567
Videos.
You can take trips home.

06:55.567 --> 06:58.233
"We."

06:58.233 --> 06:59.633
Did I miss us having
a conversation

06:59.633 --> 07:01.000
about this somehow?

07:01.000 --> 07:03.533
We bought the boat together.
We designed it together.

07:03.533 --> 07:06.467
Yeah, but we skipped
the part when we talk

07:06.467 --> 07:08.433
about when and how
we're using it.

07:08.433 --> 07:11.300
You hate this idea?

07:11.300 --> 07:15.667
No, I don't, 'cause I see
how much you love it.

07:15.667 --> 07:18.166
And I get why it would be
a once-in-a-lifetime for them.

07:18.166 --> 07:20.400
-I'm just...
[picks up plate]

07:20.400 --> 07:23.433
[sighs deeply]
...trying it on for a sec.

07:23.433 --> 07:29.033
Good. Okay, do that.
Then let's go. It hit me.

07:29.033 --> 07:33.600
Why work so hard if not to do
what we want, when we want?

