07:36.133 --> 07:37.400
[Terri] I might've
misheard earlier,

07:37.400 --> 07:40.700
but, um, did you call
the US Attorney "dude"?

07:40.700 --> 07:42.200
-Sorry?
-Back there.

07:42.200 --> 07:44.033
I think you might've said
something like,

07:44.033 --> 07:46.734
"Dude, it's perfect,"
to the US Attorney.

07:46.734 --> 07:48.200
I don't think I said "dude."

07:48.200 --> 07:50.233
I don't even remember
saying "it's perfect."

07:50.233 --> 07:52.200
-Just repeating what I heard.
-I'm not doubting you.

07:52.200 --> 07:55.166
I just mean,
I don't think...

07:55.166 --> 07:57.233
I mean...no.

07:57.233 --> 07:59.200
Yeah, I'm being
a friend here.

07:59.200 --> 08:00.467
Wow, did I actually
say "dude"?

08:00.467 --> 08:02.200
-Yeah. Mm-hmm.
-I did. I said it.

08:02.200 --> 08:04.767
The vibe at the law firm I was
at before joining the Bureau

08:04.767 --> 08:06.033
was serious but relaxed.

08:06.033 --> 08:08.500
Okay, well, this is
serious but serious.

08:08.500 --> 08:12.033
-Remove it from your vocabulary.
-I will. Stat.

08:12.033 --> 08:14.467
No, I see.

08:14.467 --> 08:17.000
Who -- who keeps
a year's rent in the bank?

08:17.000 --> 08:20.333
I've never missed a payment,
never been late at...

08:20.333 --> 08:22.767
No, I don't.
I don't have a guarantor.

08:22.767 --> 08:26.633
Then w-why show me
the apartment at all?

08:28.467 --> 08:32.433
Just hold the place
one more day, please.

08:32.433 --> 08:33.633
Thank you.

08:33.633 --> 08:36.533
I could do it.

08:38.300 --> 08:40.166
Be your guarantor.

08:40.166 --> 08:42.500
Don't listen to my calls.

08:42.500 --> 08:44.533
Don't leave your door open.

08:44.533 --> 08:46.500
How is...

08:46.500 --> 08:49.066
Look, thanks, but I wouldn't
take your parents' money

08:49.066 --> 08:51.066
even if it wasn't
against the rules here.

08:51.066 --> 08:54.000
You're not taking anything
if you don't default.

08:54.000 --> 08:55.200
You gonna default?

08:55.200 --> 08:57.100
No.

08:57.100 --> 08:59.367
You could think about it.

08:59.367 --> 09:01.300
We could ask for
a waiver or something.

09:01.300 --> 09:05.133
And, uh, it's my money.

09:05.133 --> 09:07.633
They gave it to me
when I turned 25.

09:07.633 --> 09:09.000
[whispers] So...

09:11.734 --> 09:14.266
[exhales slowly]

09:14.266 --> 09:17.400
[gasping, moaning loudly]

09:19.133 --> 09:22.066
[continues moaning,
gasping]

09:24.266 --> 09:27.467
[moans, gasps]

09:27.467 --> 09:30.033
[exhales sharply]

09:30.033 --> 09:32.066
[moans]

09:33.500 --> 09:37.500
I was up till 4 a.m.
this morning.

09:37.500 --> 09:40.467
I was watching videos
of BASE jumpers.

09:40.467 --> 09:42.367
There was this guy --

09:42.367 --> 09:47.266
he just sails from mountain
to mountain in Yosemite.

09:47.266 --> 09:51.000
It's incredible.
He just...

09:51.000 --> 09:53.000
He just takes flight.

09:53.000 --> 09:56.333
Soars over the valleys.

09:56.333 --> 09:59.233
He's weightless,
utterly free.

10:01.433 --> 10:04.433
I wanna feel what that's like
just once in my life,

10:04.433 --> 10:06.700
like I'm saying
"fuck you" to gravity.

10:08.166 --> 10:10.633
Didn't that guy die?

10:10.633 --> 10:12.600
-Yeah.
-[chuckles]

10:12.600 --> 10:14.467
Yeah, but, I mean,
he wanted to.

10:14.467 --> 10:16.100
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles]

10:19.233 --> 10:21.133
I gotta go.

10:21.133 --> 10:23.000
Come on.
Play hooky with me.

10:23.000 --> 10:25.600
I can't. I'm handling lunch.

10:25.600 --> 10:27.266
And I gotta make arrangements
for the restaurant.

10:27.266 --> 10:29.100
I can't just disappear.

10:31.200 --> 10:34.166
You sure you're
ready to do this?

10:34.166 --> 10:35.500
I didn't mean
to surprise you.

10:35.500 --> 10:39.200
Yeah, you did,
or you wouldn't have.

10:39.200 --> 10:41.333
You don't get carried away.

10:41.333 --> 10:44.633
But I know you wanted it
to be a good surprise.

10:44.633 --> 10:49.066
And it is, once I started
getting used to it.

10:51.300 --> 10:53.734
[whispers] But I do still
have to go set up for it.

10:53.734 --> 10:56.200
Okay. Go.

10:56.200 --> 10:58.533
-I'll amuse myself.
-[chuckles]

10:58.533 --> 11:01.633
Just don't go jumping
off any cliffs.

11:01.633 --> 11:03.333
I won't.

11:03.333 --> 11:05.500
Maybe I'll watch a movie.

11:05.500 --> 11:08.200
Inglourious Basterds  again?

11:08.200 --> 11:09.500
[laughs] No.

11:09.500 --> 11:12.667
I've never seen
Citizen Kane,

11:12.667 --> 11:16.100
projected, the way
you're supposed to.

11:20.500 --> 11:23.133
Perfect. I'll make a call.

11:28.633 --> 11:30.333
[Bryan] So what do we got
on the, uh, researcher?

11:30.333 --> 11:31.767
Clayton Grunwald.

11:31.767 --> 11:35.133
Farmer, agricultural scientist
for Pepsum for 20 years.

11:35.133 --> 11:38.000
One-income household, about 70K,
no travel records,

11:38.000 --> 11:40.033
no trace of Stearn in Iowa,

11:40.033 --> 11:43.100
but I don't buy a relationship
like this blooming via phone.

11:43.100 --> 11:46.233
Maybe a conference somewhere?

11:46.233 --> 11:48.233
-Neutral territory?
-Nothing.

11:48.233 --> 11:49.734
[Bryan] Then Iowa.
Stearn covered his tracks.

11:49.734 --> 11:52.266
Didn't fly, paid only cash.

11:52.266 --> 11:54.000
Maybe we pay the farmer
a visit.

11:54.000 --> 11:55.700
What, with nothing? No, no.
We -- we gotta come heavy.

11:55.700 --> 11:57.600
Otherwise, the guy says
jack shit or he --

11:57.600 --> 11:59.066
he just lawyers up.

11:59.066 --> 12:01.567
All right.

12:01.567 --> 12:03.700
What do cheap guys do?

12:03.700 --> 12:07.266
Don't look at me.
I treat my queen very well.

12:07.266 --> 12:10.667
They go dutch.
Every fuckin' time.

12:11.700 --> 12:14.700
Just to be clear...
we're frozen?

12:14.700 --> 12:17.066
We're not buying, for now.

12:17.066 --> 12:19.266
Not Carthill.
Don't fuck me like that.

12:19.266 --> 12:21.367
It's a Hondo Havlicek.
Can't miss.

12:21.367 --> 12:24.600
It is bad timing, I know.
But keep on liquidating.

12:24.600 --> 12:26.767
We were up north
of the timberline.

12:26.767 --> 12:28.333
Why are we bailing?

12:28.333 --> 12:30.033
We're not bailing.

12:30.033 --> 12:33.734
We're pruning, slowly,
so we don't scare the market.

12:33.734 --> 12:36.567
And keep this on the fucking DL.

12:36.567 --> 12:39.734
We need to be deliberate
and delicate about this.

12:39.734 --> 12:41.300
Bonsai artists.

12:41.300 --> 12:43.233
Since when do we do
delicate?

12:43.233 --> 12:45.300
Since now.

12:45.300 --> 12:47.200
Do we know how long?

12:47.200 --> 12:48.533
As long as he wants, Carly.

12:48.533 --> 12:50.500
I gotta say, I'm not
feeling this strategy.

12:50.500 --> 12:52.033
Well, then it's a good thing

12:52.033 --> 12:54.233
your feelings aren't
a fucking priority.

12:54.233 --> 12:56.333
Thank you for your time.

12:59.166 --> 13:02.033
[telephone ringing]
-[Chuck] Dale.

13:02.033 --> 13:04.166
[lowered voice] I need you
to do something for me.

13:04.166 --> 13:05.533
Yes, sir.

13:05.533 --> 13:08.033
Somewhere between "sir"
and "dude," okay?

13:08.033 --> 13:10.000
Yeah. [sighs]

13:10.000 --> 13:14.767
I need you to find a woman
named Martina Slovis.

13:14.767 --> 13:17.333
-S-L-O-V-I-S.
-[under breath] Martina Slovis.

13:17.333 --> 13:19.033
She used to live
in Cobble Hill.

13:19.033 --> 13:21.333
[pouring coffee]
-Dropped out of Brooklyn Law.

13:21.333 --> 13:24.400
And this is only
for me. Got it?

13:24.400 --> 13:27.133
You know I do.

13:27.133 --> 13:28.600
[coffeepot clatters]

13:28.600 --> 13:31.233
-[clears throat]
[bottles clink]

13:33.233 --> 13:37.233
[indistinct chatter]

13:37.233 --> 13:38.467
-Hey.
-Hmm?

13:38.467 --> 13:39.734
We got it.

13:39.734 --> 13:42.166
We ran down everything
this guy ever signed

13:42.166 --> 13:44.467
or signed up for,
and on April 25,

13:44.467 --> 13:46.533
William Stearn's
Silver Elite card

13:46.533 --> 13:48.633
was logged into
the Downtown Marriott

13:48.633 --> 13:50.367
in Des Moines, Iowa.

13:50.367 --> 13:52.166
Now he paid cash
for the hotel room,

13:52.166 --> 13:54.467
but he couldn't turn down
the reward points.

13:54.467 --> 13:57.633
[laughs] Every man is
a junkie for something.

13:57.633 --> 13:59.266
Find it, find him,
and you did.

13:59.266 --> 14:00.734
-Yeah.
-Excellent.

14:00.734 --> 14:02.500
Here's our researcher.

14:02.500 --> 14:03.600
Clayton Grunwald.

14:03.600 --> 14:05.600
We're heading to Iowa
to jump him.

14:05.600 --> 14:07.734
Aiming to have an affidavit
in your hands by Friday.

14:07.734 --> 14:09.233
-Yeah.
-Hmm.

14:09.233 --> 14:11.066
Christ.

14:11.066 --> 14:12.266
Hello, Chuck.

14:12.266 --> 14:14.000
I'm sorry.
We had a sit-down scheduled.

14:14.000 --> 14:16.533
-Can we talk?
-It's okay.

14:16.533 --> 14:19.600
-You want him here?
-What have I got to hide?

